THOUGHT: Given the previous task families, I want to propose a task that combines linguistic creativity, scientific knowledge, and problem-solving skills. The task will involve creating and solving scientific "what if" scenarios, which will test the model's ability to apply scientific principles creatively and reason through complex, hypothetical situations. This task is novel compared to the previous ones as it focuses on scientific extrapolation and creative problem-solving in a unique format. I believe this task will be challenging for the model, as it requires a deep understanding of scientific principles and the ability to apply them in unconventional ways. An LLM judge would be suitable for scoring this task, as it requires evaluating the scientific accuracy, creativity, and logical consistency of the responses.

